        <page n="02" image="va.au.ss.1863.04.21.02">
            <div type="a">
                <column>1</column>
                <head>Milroy in Winchester - A Family Driven from Home.</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Article asserts tha Lloyd Logan's family was driven from their elegant home
                    to be occupied by Gen. Milroy and his family.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>2</column>
                <head>Supplies for the Army</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Baldwin</ln>
                        <fn>John B.</fn>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf/>
                    </name>
                </names>
                <summary>Item calls attention to the President's address and the speech of John
                    Baldwin. Article also urges citizens to put selfish interests behind them and
                    work for the good of the war effort.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>2</column>
                <head>A Soldier of Augusta</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer>He requests us to make this statement that the friends of the deceased may
                    be able to designate which Hanger it was.</trailer>
                <names>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Taylor</ln>
                        <fn>William</fn>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf/>
                    </name>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Hanger</ln>
                        <fn/>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf>Mr.</pf>
                    </name>
                </names>
                <summary>Item reports that an Augusta soldier named Hanger became, while riding with
                    another soldier, mired in a swamp and died.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look>x</look>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>3</column>
                <head>For Congress</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Baldwin</ln>
                        <fn>John B.</fn>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf/>
                    </name>
                </names>
                <summary>The Spectator endorses John Baldwin for Congress.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>3</column>
                <head>The Starvation Campaign</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt>Every farmer should engage in the patriotic labor of raising whatever may
                    be used to sustain the lives of our soldiers and feed the horses of our armies.</excerpt>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Article encourages farmers to grow food crops for the war effort.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
